      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "### \u2139\ufe0f About This Report\nFIS return file results matched back to submitted batch records. Sourced from **`reporting.fact_reconciliation`** joined to **`reporting.dim_member`**.\n\n| Column | Source | Meaning |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| Result Code | `fact_reconciliation.fis_result_code` | `000` = success. Any other value is a FIS rejection code |\n| Result Message | `fact_reconciliation.fis_result_message` | Human-readable FIS response text |\n| Status | `fact_reconciliation.reconciliation_status` | MATCHED = FIS accepted (code=000). UNMATCHED = FIS rejected |\n| Batch File ID | `fact_reconciliation.batch_file_id` | Links to the outbound batch file sent to FIS |\n| Row Sequence | `fact_reconciliation.row_sequence_number` | Position of this record within the batch file |\n| Reconciled Date | `fact_reconciliation.reconciled_at` | When Stage 7 processed the FIS return file |\n\n> **MATCHED** = FIS accepted the enrollment and assigned FIS Person ID, CUID, and Card ID. These identifiers are stamped onto `dim_member` and `dim_card` by Stage 7.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.4.3",
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
